Product name: Antique Game Board. 1800s Telegraph Boy. McLoughlin Bros. Office, Game Room Wall Art. Victorian Parlor Game. Gift for College Grad, MBA.
Description:
Colorful antique game board that shows the way from Telegraph Boy to President of the company.  Move up in the ranks as you go around the board.  Landing on Ambition, Integrity or Promptness helps move you forward, but watch out because Loitering and Laziness will send you backwards. Personal fav is "Stupidity", which sends you back to "Carelessness."  Great office or game room decor, and a wonderful gift for the business school grad.
16 1/4" x 17".
The spinner is missing from the lower right corner. 
In nice vintage condition with light surface and edge wear. The wear is more apparent on the backside edges of the board, rather than the playing side. Bold orange, reds, golds and greens, with no apparent fading. Copyright 1888, McLoughlin Bros. The company, known for its chromolithographic artwork, was founded in 1858 and sold to Milton Bradley in 1920.

Product name: Antique Chinese Grayish Green Twisted Rope Jade Bangle Bracelet - Natural Green Jade Bangle - Asian Antique Jade Collectibles
Description:
Jade has had mystical significance since the Neolithic Age which began 10,000 years ago. Most sophisticated Neolithic settlements date to 3000 BC. Various cultures began to develop around the Yellow and Yangtze rivers. Settlements in the north were sparse, but appear to have had contact with both extreme northern peoples and with those in the southern areas around the areas of Xi'an and Anyang. Interesting similarities in bronze art extend from the northern Mongolian regions down into Yunnan. During the late Neolithic period the Yan people began to form a system culture. At the same time, the Han people were developing their culture around Anyang.
Chinese people believed jade had supernatural power. Using jade wares & jade ornaments could resist invasion of evil influence, avoid evil apparitions, secure safety & auspiciousness. 
Jade was highly regulated in ancient China. It is the second strongest mineral next to diamond and was once considered more valuable than gold.
Jade – a gemstone of unique symbolic energy, and unique in the myths that surround it and is thought to be calming to the nervous system, perfectly for calming the hot-tempered.
It also represents life and growth.

Description:
"The Standard Book of Spells is a collection of spell books written by Miranda Goshawk that covers a variety of magical subjects. This volume includes many of the most important spells found in each grade of the Standard Book of Spells as well as spells from other prolific books such as Achievements in Charming and A Guide to Advanced Transfiguration. This edition of The Standard Book of Spells is developed in particular for use at Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry."
This is an 8.25" x 10.75" hardcover bound book with a paper (not leather) book sleeve. Each entry includes the spell name, source, type, pronunciation, description and etymology and when applicable some history regarding the spell. Each letter of the alphabet is included in the book even if there is no spell listed that starts with that letter (J,K,X,Y,Z). The book has no illustrations but has periodic Celtic markings.
This volume is perfect for any Witch or Wizard in training.
